data.content:
Created both files. Here's how it works:

- **Generic** — `@typeparam TItem` lets it work with any type.
- **Internal copy** — `SetParametersAsync` creates a new `List<TItem>` from the incoming `Items`, so the parent's list is never mutated.
- **Move Up / Move Down** buttons swap adjacent items and fire `OnOrderChanged` with a read-only snapshot.
- Buttons are disabled at the list boundaries (first item can't move up, last can't move down).

**Usage matches your example:**

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = new() { /* ... */ };

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
